hrough a sequence of higher daily closes into the 0.8135\u20130.8149 area by late June and again on 13 July, where the most recent swing high printed at 0.8149. That level has twice rejected further upside, and the subsequent pullbacks \u2014 including a sharp two-day retreat to 0.8035 in early July \u2014 have kept the broader picture rangebound rather than trending. The four identified support zones all sit well below current price, clustered between 0.7777 and 0.7939, and none has been tested in the current leg. They represent prior reaction zones where buyers have historically re-engaged, but their distance from spot means they are structural reference points rather than immediately actionable context for today's session.\n\nThe intraday picture on the H1 chart is equally telling. Price pushed up to 0.8097 in the early Asian session before fading steadily through the European morning and into the afternoon, giving back roughly 30 pips to settle around 0.8065\u20130.8070 by the close of the latest candle. The fade has been orderly \u2014 no sharp impulse lower, simply a drift \u2014 which is consistent with end-of-week positioning and a lack of fresh catalysts. The 0.8090\u20130.8095 area, where the pair stalled on multiple H1 attempts today, now reads as a near-term intraday resistance band. Below spot, the 0.8065 area has offered mild support across the past hour; a clean break beneath that on the H1 would open a look at 0.8045, the lower end of the week's consolidation.\n\nThe economic calendar is empty for today's session, which removes the prospect of data-driven volatility and reinforces the likelihood of a quiet, range-bound close to the week. Without a macro catalyst, the pair is likely to remain anchored to the 0.8065\u20130.8095 intraday range unless broader risk sentiment or dollar flows shift materially into the New York close.\n\nThe read that would change the picture: a daily close above 0.8149 \u2014 the twin swing high from late June and 13 July \u2014 would materially strengthen the case for a bullish continuation scenario. Conversely, a sustained break below 0.8035, the early-July structure low, would undermine the recovery narrative and bring the 0.7939 prior reaction zone back into focus as the next meaningful reference on the daily chart.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}